In December 1881 (Meiji 14), parishioners of Kanomi Shrine petitioned for the separation of the Inner Shrine's auxiliary shrine and the village shrine<ref name="st6">Sakurai (1991): p.276</ref>. The residents of Kanomi claimed that the auxiliary shrine and the village shrine, originally having different locations and deities, had been conflated since 1871, effectively placing them under the control of the Jingū, restricting local management<ref name="st6"/>. They presented documents showing that the village shrine "Hachioji Shrine" had been renamed "Kanomi Shrine" in 1870 (Meiji 3), with its deity changed to match that of Kanomi Shrine<ref name="st7">Sakurai (1991): p.277</ref>. After discussions among the Jingū, Mie Prefectural Office, and Ministry of Home Affairs, it was decided in February 1886 (Meiji 19) to separate the auxiliary shrine and the village shrine<ref name="st7"/>.
No separation movement was recorded for Mike Shrine, suggesting there were no issues regarding its dual jurisdiction<ref>Sakurai (1991): p.278</ref>.
== Access == The shrine is located along a farm road<ref name="ic"/>. There are no parking facilities nearby.
; Public Transportation * Approximately a 16-minute walk (about 1.3 km) from {{ill|Isuzugaoka Station|ja|五十鈴ケ丘駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isuzugaoka Station|qq=}} on the {{ill|Sangū Line|ja|参宮線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sangū Line|qq=}} operated by JR Central. * From {{ill|Isuzugawa Station|ja|五十鈴川駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isuzugawa Station|qq=}} on the {{ill|Kintetsu Toba Line|ja|Toba Line|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kintetsu Toba Line|qq=}}, take the "Kanomi-Asama Route" {{ill|community bus|ja|コミュニティバス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/community bus|qq=}} (Okage Bus), get off at "Higashi Kanomi" bus stop, and walk about 3 minutes (approx. 270 m), or get off at "Nishi Kanomi" bus stop and walk about 3 minutes (approx. 320 m).
; By Car * About 2 minutes (approx. 820 m) heading east from the "Kanomi Town" intersection on National Route 23. * Approximately 4 minutes (about 1.5 km) from {{ill|Asama Interchange|ja|朝熊インターチェンジ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asama Interchange|qq=}} on the {{ill|Ise Futami Toba Toll Road|ja|伊勢二見鳥羽有料道路|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ise Futami Toba Toll Road|qq=}}. == References == {{Reflist|2}}
